rComments: Avoid taking this class at all possible. Sounds like a very interesting class however she barely touches base on the subject. Doesn't follow the Course Description. Has made the whole course about her ethnicity and studying it. Disrespected the class when we didn't properly understand her group project assignment. Assignments not relevant to course

At first glance, the course sounds very interesting. However, it soon becomes very boring, partly because of the heavy course-load, but mostly because of how monotonic prof Dina is. For the group project, the professor didn't give clear guidelines, but was furious when her students misunderstood the assignment. Pls avoid taking this class.

The class name sounds that the course will be so much interesting, but it actually not and it will much lower than your expectation. prof doesn't provide a rubric for the written work and her expectation is very unclear. Her tone of speaking about the class group project performance was very acceptable. Please avoid her or don't take her classes.
Don't have much to say different than everyone else. Worst teacher ever. How come university hired someone who has no doctorate and puts professor beside her name? AVOID AT ALL COST!

She relies so heavily on the textbook, it is honestly so upsetting to see someone just restate everything she made you read in the week prior. Her lectures are awful. They don't teach you anything and I suggest you skip them, as your brain cells are precious and needed for other courses. Particular is the word she uses for 99% of the lecture, Run.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read', 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: I honestly can't decide if I hated the prof or the course! It was dreadful. The material was dreadful! I think we talked about the telegraph for a whole month. She is soooo monotone! Her tests are so hard! She includes both lecture and text materials so you really have to pay attention to everything she says. And her tests consist of random things

I had a great experience with this Prof. She is a great lecturer and was super helpful when I had questions. There was a lot of group work but I had a good group so I guess I lucked out in the end. Overall, I had to work for the grade I received but it was well worth it in the end!

One of the most disorganized classes I have ever attended in my 4 years at university. The group project ended up being worth 70% of your grade and if you got a bad group... good luck. The midterm wasn't until mid November so we did not receive 1 grade before November 15, therefore too late to drop the class. Do not recommend this professor.

The final exam (worth 55%) really messed me up bringing my A- down to a C+. The final exam consisted of multiple choice and short answers, the short answers were worth 70% of the exam and were incredibly specific when she had told us we did not need to study details. A bummer really :( almost as if she was trying to deceive students.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Test heavy', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: She does not give specific detail about the assignments and then gives you a bad mark on something she told you to do. Her midterm exam was impossible, even if you studied, the most random things were asked and they were worth a lot. Almost my entire group failed or almost failed (and we all studied enough). She makes your life difficult.

You will use launchpad which is annoying because the website is hard to use. Exam was almost 60 percent. Make sure you go to class before the mid term and exam because she gives some hints. She makes you work for a good mark.

She is stingy in offering students help, like when I turned to her, she didn't give my any helpful suggestions. A lot of work are done by her TAs. Exams of her courses guaranteed studendts to fail. She is just a promoter who helps the university to gain more tuitions.

The final is so 'amazing' that there is one concept which is never mentioned in the textbook and lectures occured. The worse is, this concept accounted for 40% of the final exam; 100 multiple choice questions accounted for 30% only. Her lectures are not clear as well. Please STAY AWAY from this prof!!!!

Worst Professor that I have ever had. The final and midterm were extremely difficult and worse 85% in total. Which means you have no chance to get a good mark if you did bad on exam. She mean to fail students on purpose, one short answer topic that she never taught before worse 40% on the final exam.

This final is by far the most awfully unexpected, unorganized exam Ive ever written. It consists of a very unfair marking scheme, and covers the slightest bits of information. Very detailed oriented, really makes you think, and overall a very unfair exam. Come to class, take detailed notes on EVERYTHING and read your textbook!! SHOOK!!

The structure of her class in relation to midterms and finals is virtually guaranteed to make students fail. Her final exam had a section based on one topic that was worth 40%. That means that if you aced the exam but didn't study this one small topic, your highest possible mark would be 60%. That is ridiculous and completely unfair to students.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Dont be fooled by how simple the material seems in the beginning. As the months go on the information gets heavier and heavier. It may feel like it makes sense and that it is easy to take in. But with all my years in college and uni, this final was the worst final I have ever had to go through. It looked like a 5 year old copy pasted the question
Although she talks about her ppt during class, she doesn't explain the concept thoroughly. The content of the class is too heavy and difficult for a student who has just begun to learn communication.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things', 'Test heavy']

rComments: One of my 4th year marketing profs told me not to take this class & he was right. This was the worst class I've ever taken. The content was irrelevant, prof is AWFUL, & the grading is insane. I've never cared enough to rate a prof on this website until today. I took this as an "easy" elective. It will be my worst mark since 2nd-year.

Most useless prof I've ever had. I asked to book an appointment with her and she refused to speak with us and told us to go to the TAs. Even bettter, the TAs won't respond to my emails :) By far the worst mark I've gotten in university and this is my elective <3 DO NOT TAKE THIS COURSE. AVOID IT AND THIS PROF AT ALL COSTS.
Worse professor I've ever had. Boring lectures, and is no help and leaves everything to the TA's to grade. Does not care about her students, and the TA's are less than helpful.
The exam is extremely difficult and not related to what she taught. Stay away from this professor...

This is a fun class to attend, the professor is very charismatic and unique. The course has interesting topics and she includes outside sources to make it extra interesting. The book comes in handy for the Launchpad quizzes and HW. As long as you pay attention in class, you're good to go.
Horrible professor,, avoid at all costs

She rambles A LOT. says 100 words about something that could easily be said in 10. Exam was multiple choice, participation matters. sometimes i dont even know where she was going when she was explaining something. would not take again, dont recommend her. nice person though.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Test heavy', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Professor Salha made a course that could have been very dry and very boring, a lot more tolerable. There were two midterms (10% and 20%) and the rest was group work (an essay proposal, presentation and final paper). Choose your group wisely....
Easy A - majority of the course is online assignments (group), which are short and not at all difficult. Final exam is short answer questions.

Dina is a good prof who cares about her students and is super knowledgable. Brings snacks to class often (yay) and her tests and assignments reflect the class content very closely. HOWEVER she has very little concept of time. Don't take a class with her if you have another one right after, you'll be late every time.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Graded by few things', 'Group projects']

rComments: I am livid right now at the use of a terrible system called "launchpad" that is essentially a spy tool for the prof and TA to monitor the students progress in studying the material for the course. The software doesn't work 50-75% of the time so by the first midterm I've wasted hours on it. Also, tons of mini assignments without clear deadlines

Probably the worst prof I ever had and will have. Super hard, was very rude and obnoxious when you asked for help, was even rude to our TA! Exams barely reflect anything we learned in class. Goes off on many tangents, and the class is extremely dry and boring. If you can take discussion groups provided for the faculty I suggest you do so!

Although she is very knowledgeable in in the subject matter. I found the subject to be extremely dry given the potential this course has. It seem dated and the lectures seemed to last for hours. This course need a really solid update.

Amazing professor. Very interested in her topic, and it's visible. A lot of little assignments, but they are all incredibly fair and very manageable. Group project, but if you find a good group (she gives you plenty of time) you'll enjoy it. Final is a group paper.

Professor Salha's class was okay. The only grades are the midterm and final exam, so there isn't much of a chance to boost your mark. She also asked very specific questions from the textbook, sometimes the answers are found in the caption to a photo in the text. Overall not bad, her lectures were interesting and applicable to everyday life.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Respected', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: I've had Dina before & loved her. She is very easy going & understanding of the busy student lifestyle. She changed the final exam to a final paper which my group already started so it was easy. Got 100%. I took this course before with another prof & failed & took it with her & got an A+. Definitely recommend for an easy A & an entertaining class.

Great prof! She perfectly balances her lectures between class content and informal conversations. I learned ALOT from CMN3109 and I think this is because of the way she teaches. She gives valuable feedback (use it!). Really enjoyed having her as a prof. Would take again.
DO NOT TAKE HER IF YOU HAVE THE CHOICE!

Amazing lecturer- knows the material, gives plenty of examples& relates it back to modern day society Only 1 midterm& 1 final- do not study the night before! If you follow everything she says, you'll do fine (go to the study groups, do the readings...) Readings were irrelevant, long& boring; however, still important and will be tested on it

Knows tons about her subject but fails badly at isolating what's important, so you end up covering like, two courses' worth of material. Comes off lazy. She assigns up to 4 textbook chapters a week. Don't read entire chapter (majority is unrelated) just memorize key definitions. Important info always comes up at END of lecture so don't leave early.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: She's really nice, but her lectures are really boring and seem to drag on forever. She cancelled a lot of our classes, seemed bored herself, or just had the TA teach, but don't let that fool you. Her midterm was worth 40% and the final is 60%, and she makes her multiple choice hard, they trick you or are super specific.

Professor Salha's lectures are interesting & engaging. She gives a lot of info, so be prepared to take notes on everything she says. Don't bother taking notes on the slides; they're available online. Readings are important, so don't skip them. Make sure all your notes are ready a week before exams. Do study dates & names.

Professor Salha is very disrespectful towards her students and will make you feel stupid if you don't understand a concept. She had one midterm of 40 multiple choice worth 40% (only allowed 1 hour) which should be easy since it's communication.. NOPE. Hardest exam in my university career. I don't have enough characters to say how much I hate her.

This course is horrible. I can't understand or grasp any of the theories in class because I'm too confused the whole time. The quiz was very hard with over half the class failing it because it was too hard.
As long as you either read the textbook or go to class, you'll do well.

Extremely unclear expectations for grades. She doesn't explain assignments. I understand that you can't have your hand held at Uni but she just doesn't care. 'Deal with it yourself' is her catchphrase. There is alot of group work because the prof is lazy and doesn't wanna mark individually. Your mark will suffer for her laziness and she won't care.

After two classes, I can say she teaches very well but you have to at least care about communications to pass. Attendance, midterm, final & group project. Midterm & final are a few long-answer questions (2-3pgs) on lectures & readings. Group projects do well with creativity. Know your theories, attend class enough, bit of effort and you're golden.
Extremely high expectations and difficult midterms. Lots of group work. I would avoid.
Pretty poor lecturer. Doesn't explain class material and exams/assignments don't reflect class material.
I got an A in this class, although there are so many group works but I was so lucky because my group members were great. She gave really high marks on videos

Good prof, lectures were fine and pretty interesting and so was the subject material. However, she did a midterm worth 50% and a final worth 50% with no opportunities to make up for the grades. Would take her class again.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Accessible outside class', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: There are only two multiple choices exams for the course, each one count for 50% of the final mark. Her mid-term are fairly easy, questions are from both lectures and the textbook. For the textbook part, you only need to know the definition of key terms. The final is very difficult. Many questions are not course related.

Very nice person and easy to talk with, but doesn't teach in a way that's easy to understand or remember the material. If you skip classes you won't pass. Half of the test is on readings, and about 40 % of the exam is on the readings. Would love to take her again if she worked on her teaching style, she gives too much information than necessary.

Seems like a pretty nice person. Her lectures however do get very long and kinda boring. Shes also  a pretty tough grader. We had one midterm of 60 multiple choice questions and a final of 160 multiple choice questions. Dont let this foul you though, they are quite a few tricks in these exams and for the final you only have 2 hours instead of 3.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Lots of homework', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Disorganized professor, seems like she made up the assignments and expectations as she went.

Prof. Salha is a great lecturer and a kind person. Some theoretical concepts are heavy so it's important to attend class. Expectations for assignments could be clearer. Make sure you read thoroughly and attend lectures to do well on her tests. Highly willing to answer questions and provide feedback.

Nice prof, you can tell she enjoys her subject but if you don't go to class, you'll be lost. Her lecture slides are very vague, so don't depend on them. Her midterm wasn't incredibly difficult, but it wasn't easy either. Make sure you attend class, read the book and take good notes.

Lots of group work, put in the effort & you'll do fine. Go to her office hours as a group & for group paper and will get lots of feedback (not clear in class). The only annoying thing was the only midterm being so late in the semester, so there was a lot of material (20%). Overall the course was pretty interesting! She also brings lots of snacks!
Avoid this prof. She is extremely unclear in her explanations and what she expects from students. Group project is a nightmare. Boring material and rude prof.

She is very disorganized and unclear of her expectations, she was also very rude to students on many occasions which was hurtful. Group project was not fun and marks are not well reflective of your actual intellectual abilities

poorly organized professor, syllabus and grading is unclear. For some assignments she clearly does not know what she is looking for. The reliance on group projects is likely also a result of her not wanting to mark as many assignments. Be careful with who you pick for a group (Comm students are often lazy) could hurt mark or have u do everything

Prof Salha is a kind human being with good intentions. She is passionate about her work and you can tell she cares. However her slides can be vague and only touch on a few point but she'll discuss them for an hour. Often goes very deep in topic discussion. She is very approachable. In my opinion the course needs major reworking.

Although she is an amazing lecturer and a very interesting woman, this class was so unorganized and expectations were not clear. Midterms were super tough and based on things that were mentioned once. But the group project was a good grade saver
I found her material and teaching style kind of dry, she could have explained some things better. Her slides were difficult to decipher, make sure you take your own notes.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'So many papers', 'Group projects']

rComments: Midterms and exams are fair but can be tough,  and you need to attend class in order to do well.

Great Prof. She tried Echo360 but won't be using it again until it is more reliable. It was good practice for midterms however. You will need the textbook. Quizzes are fair and final exam was fair. Great lecturer, very funny.

Found this class extremely disorganized and not enjoyable. She only taught for three weeks of the semester and was extremely unhelpful when visited during her office hours concerning the group project. Will not take a class with her again.

I don't often like my profs - actually I never do, but I loved her. I have a crippling anxiety disorder and was ready to drop the class when I saw group projects AND oral presentations together - but the fashion in which she assigned it made it awesome, I even made new friends from the class. She gave amazing feedback on our proposal paper. A+ prof

She uses echo360 to put her slides up on and keep track of participation. She's really funny and her classes are interesting and the information is up-to-date with media. I never bought a textbook for this class which I regret because it is needed, although I still got a B- in the class from studying just her slides. You get to keep old midterms.

She's a nice person but her class is NOT easy. I felt like I had to learn two sets of material because she tests you on both the lectures and the readings. Which aren't very similar and is why you need to really take notes on the readings. Despite all of this, she's a really nice lady and funny too.

Multiple choice exams are extremely difficult. Most are out of A-E and she puts answers like: A&B or C&D, making you question your answer, even though you thought you knew. Potential to be a good course... taking notes is essential and so is reading the textbook. She is a good speaker, sometimes funny. But not an easy A

Wonderful woman but not an easy course. The group project is so hard to do well on and will take up SO MUCH of your time. The first midterm is way harder than the second one. Make sure you do your readings for these or you WILL NOT PASS. Lectures are long and nothing is stressed, which makes exams hard. Pay attention to guest speakers

She's an awesome professor, the course itself needs reworking.  There is a lot of heavy theory here, but she's good at explaining it simply, attendance is 100% mandatory if you want to understand and pass. Tests are super small, but the readings are insanely large, beware of this. Group projects are tough & graded critically. Profgreat, coursemeh

Very nice teacher, but some concepts thought in class and most of the lectures can be hard to understand. You can't skip the lectures as they represent half of the points in each test (book + text pack )  But she is a fair grader and will be available to answer any question you may have
Great prof. Funny and the content was relevant. Great to work with outside the classroom if you had additional questions or needed feedback on something.
Really great prof. She is so interesting to listen to and always has great ideas. Her class is not too difficult if you follow along.

Read the textbook, go to class and reach out when you need help will lead to success in Dina's classes. She is willing to help students succeed if you take it upon yourself and approach her. Her lectures are good and she is up-to-date on popular culture.

I really enjoyed her class. she is really nice and she discusses important and interesting topics. She does not a final exam but a paper instead and a visual project that is really fun to work on. the comments on the our work is really clear and helpful. I would definitely recommend this class.

Great prof! Very helpful if you actually go to her office hours. If you put in the effort, she will make it worth your while. If you just go to the lectures, you will not succeed. I got an A+ because I went to her office every week or second week just to even clarify or review... even if I didn't have questions.

Not a hard course, but ended up being very stressful. Second time with this professor. The quiz structures are brutal to study for. Group paper instead of a final, which has its pros and cons. Pretty tough marker on the proposal and presentations. I learned quite a bit in this course and still  did well. But it was stressful.

Love her class and her! Passionate about advertising and the effects of media. Explains everything clearly, great teaching style. Very open to questions, opinions & debate. If I had the option of taking every single CMN course with her, I would. She is my queen
Over all very good class, you need to do lots of reading and preparation.
Very challenging class, you have to be very attentive to the theories and reading materials. Don't take this course if you trying to get an easy grade.

As others mentioned, she knows her stuff, but a hard marker on assignments, papers and exams. Exams are essay based, no mc questions at all. Her exam questions are super specific! Read your textbooks if you wanna pass this class.

One of the best professors I've ever had. She is super passionate in the field of communication and extremely qualified. Her research and work are also very interesting. I'm finishing my third year now and have made sure I've had her at least once every year because of how much I liked her in my first year. Can't say enough good things about her!

Nice prof, but her midterms and exams are super specific! She's very monotone, talks a lot and kinda puts you to sleep. Most people in this class never paid attention and it was clear. Her midterms are killer, we even had to study the syllabus, wouldn't suggest it as an elective with this prof!

Boring class, however if you show up to most lectures and read over her powerpoints before the quizzes it's fairly easy.  Would only reccomend this class to students who need some extra sleep during the day or just need a straight forward class to boost GPA.
Alright professor. Her lectures can be very boring. Relies a lot on the textbook. Mandatory attendance.

The structure and the content of lectures are good till 2/3 of semester, but in the end, everybody feels the lack of source- many repetitions, even borrowing from last semester,consecutive video presentations. Contrary to her big argument on <empathy>, her <empathy> to give helpful advice for students is the question.

The midterm was supposed to be from both lectures and readings, but when I got to the midterm, it was 100% readings. One of the text books is the most boring thing you will ever read, and thats why everyone failed. Final "exam" is a group paper which you have a month or so to complete, so that makes up for the crappy midterms.

Indeed she is not the worst prof, although her exams are extremely hard even you read all the assigned readings, you could still get a F on midterm. This is what I learned from advertising class, if you want to survive, avoid her!!!!

Structure of the class is fine, but she mixes her other classes into others thinking you've learnt or not learnt concepts. Impossible to get a hold of if you have questions. Never posts things on VC when she says. Questions on tests DO NOT make sense, and in every test there is at least one section that the TAs mess up on. Avoid this if you can!!

Never again. Nice enough, knows the subject, but she's not a good prof. It's clear her students aren't her priority either...my grades are ALWAYS posted late (still waiting on one from Oct, it's now Dec). Office hours? often cancels them or just isn't there. I've tried going twice, she wasn't there. Dont buy the books, waste of $ you dont need them

Looking back, she wasn't a bad prof. I didn't like the class, but her slide shows are easy to follow. She doesn't post much online, so attendance is pretty mandatory in order to do well. Average prof.

Do the readings, know the major theories and know the movies for the first midterm. Second midterm do the readings, know your movies, and the guest speakers. Awesome class, don't know how you can't get an A. Gives really good feedback to the proposal, TA was the best I've had in University, was very kind and easy to talk to.

Great Teacher! Interesting topics with many different point of views on communication industry. Her lectures were clear and the content of the course, as a whole, was fairly easy. Unlike a some teachers, she invited the class to share their opinions. She also made her best to make the class interesting. Best class of my semester.

The prof relayed so much on the T.A-who was obviously inadequate to preform her job. The course had two exams, a  proposal, and a paper. The Exams were absolutely ridiculous! the Exam had questions like "on page 434 the author proposes a theory discuss that theory" and the TA corrects with a vengeance! AVOID her!!

She knows a lot about her subject. Her lectures were extremely boring, but her quizzes were fair and she tells you mostly what will be on it. You need to do the readings as about half of each quiz covers the readings. Pretty easy, but very boring

CMN 1160, 2173, 2160, 3104 In all of these classes, the professor is very clear as to her requirements. She is very easy and straightforward. Follow her instrucitons and syllabus and you will get the marks. I you show up to about 60% of classes (varies dependent on course) you can generally attain a B. If you want your A then go to her classes.
Good class but I fall asleep almost every time because she's so not into it
I had her for a few classes. I really dislike the communication classes but loved her. I would recommend her any day

i'm surprised she doesn't have more ratings. i've had Salha for two classes now and i intend to take a third. she always makes herself available in office hours and her tests are pretty easy if you make an effort to study. plus she lets us get off early, watch many videos/clips and she explains clearly!

This class was ridiculous. The professor focused entirely on Feminism and Racism in the course. The slides often don't make sense and are incoherent, and she has a lot of grammar and spelling mistakes...that just bothers me.
Good professor. Slides are clear as are expectations. Brings an interesting perspective on communications that's different from the standard European one presented by most professors.

awesome class. prof really knows her stuff and has done a lot of work in the field. she's extremely helpful outside of class and is mostly always available for office hours. the midterms and exams are not incredibly easy but they're fair!

Awful teacher. She insisted that we use her own definitions of general communications terms in all exams. This was a 2nd general theories class! None of the definitions or theories were her own! She didn't cover anything Communications related after the midterm, she focused entirely on feminism and racism. Complete waste of time.
